BAexMSiKJ2g.title: Let’s Change Lives
BAexMSiKJ2g.description:
On my birthday this year, I am proud to introduce Unicorn Island Fund (@unicornisland). Since the beginning of my career (and life, tbh), I’ve been an advocate for gender equity. Over the past several years I’ve had countless meetings, attended conferences, traveled the world, done field visits, and educated myself on the issues girls and women face. I always knew I wanted to create something to champion girls’ rights. It took years, significant investment of time, money, and resources, finding the right team and navigating a lot of red tape, but now it’s finally here. And I’m thrilled!
 
The reality is, there is no place on Earth where women are treated equal to men. Gender norms and beliefs have significant implications (as we’ve seen via disparities in education, employment and health).
 
Unicorn Island Fund’s work is centered on the belief that the stories we tell have the power to change culture, advance equity and transform the way the world sees and values people who have been underrepresented and underestimated for far too long. We will be creating groundbreaking content, directly investing in voices and partnering with others who share our vision.
 
For us, social and gender equity is more than a hope, dream or slogan – it’s a reality in progress. And this is where I need your help.
 
My birthday wish this year - a donation to Unicorn Island Fund to help girls live life without limits. But you won’t be giving alone. Today until September 26, for every $1 YOU donate, I will personally match dollar for dollar up to $34K. And on International Day of the Girl (Oct 11), I’ll announce OUR very first Unicorn Island Fund grants to organizations helping to change how girls are seen, heard and valued. 
 
Donate from anywhere in the world at UnicornIsland.com or at 
https://secure.donationpay.org/unicornislandfund/ 

We’ve also set up a Facebook fundraiser. 
 
You might see Social Impact Fund as the name of the nonprofit for donations. If you do, that’s great – you’re in the right spot! Unicorn Island Fund is a sponsored program of the Social Impact Fund, a 501c3 charitable organization. 100% of donations made to Social Impact Fund go to Unicorn Island Fund.

C487eGb2eNk.title: Lilly Singh - Voices
C487eGb2eNk.description:
Our mind is an intricate house filled with secrets, stories and levels. In the rooms of that house live our voices, the ones that whisper to us throughout the day. Being a good person doesn’t mean you don’t have evil voices, it just means you’ve learned to navigate through them. We all have these voices that compete within us, contradicting each other, trying to pull us in different directions. Your ego fights your loneliness. Your desire for love fights your insecurities. Your silly ways seem ideal until your mind opens to those who are suffering around the world. We’re constantly hearing our voices and therefore it’s in our best interest to befriend them. But true strength lies in deciding which of our voices govern our actions and which ones define us. It’s not about having voices in our head, it’s about what we do with them. These are my voices.
_______

Catch Lilly performing "Voices" live at YouTube Fanfest Toronto on Saturday, August 13th at the Molson Amphitheater.

HFpPunTg8JY.title: HOW TO BE A BAWSE | Book by Lilly Singh
HFpPunTg8JY.description:
How To Be A Bawse available for pre-order now:
http://www.LillySinghBook.com #BawseBook 

It’s with great excitement and pride that I announce my debut book, “How To Be a Bawse.”

Although this book will be completed over the course of a year, the lessons that fill each page took a lifetime to learn and understand. If you follow my career, you know that I often speak about a difficult time in my life when I was depressed and lifeless. This book isn’t the story of my depression, nor is it a story about my recovery. This book isn’t about me, it’s about a fight. A fight that every single one of us is experiencing, whether it’s against our mind, our health, our relationships, our bank accounts or the society we live in.
 
Sometimes we start to lose those fights and we lose faith that we’ll be able to gain everything we hope for in life; we start to accept defeat and settle for mediocrity. This book is a giant middle finger to those doubts and that voice inside that says “You can’t do it”.  You won’t find any cute quotes or fairytale messages here, because fluffy clichés don’t bring success, there's plenty of that floating around Tumblr already. This book is filled with honest, hard-hitting, practical guidelines and tips that will build you up, call you out when need be, and encourage you to work hard for the success you deserve. 
 
#BawseBook will not teach you how to survive life, because I don’t want you to simply survive. You are not in the middle of the ocean, floating on a door, holding on to Jack and waiting for someone to come and rescue you. You can do more than that. You have a toolbox filled with confidence, intelligence, power and resilience. You will not just survive, you will conquer… like a Bawse.
 
On March 28th, 2017, say goodbye to the version of yourself that is full of doubts and fears, and say hello to your inner Bawse.

localized.title: HOW TO BE A BAWSE | Book by Lilly Singh
localized.description:
How To Be A Bawse available for pre-order now:
http://www.LillySinghBook.com #BawseBook 

It’s with great excitement and pride that I announce my debut book, “How To Be a Bawse.”

Although this book will be completed over the course of a year, the lessons that fill each page took a lifetime to learn and understand. If you follow my career, you know that I often speak about a difficult time in my life when I was depressed and lifeless. This book isn’t the story of my depression, nor is it a story about my recovery. This book isn’t about me, it’s about a fight. A fight that every single one of us is experiencing, whether it’s against our mind, our health, our relationships, our bank accounts or the society we live in.
 
Sometimes we start to lose those fights and we lose faith that we’ll be able to gain everything we hope for in life; we start to accept defeat and settle for mediocrity. This book is a giant middle finger to those doubts and that voice inside that says “You can’t do it”.  You won’t find any cute quotes or fairytale messages here, because fluffy clichés don’t bring success, there's plenty of that floating around Tumblr already. This book is filled with honest, hard-hitting, practical guidelines and tips that will build you up, call you out when need be, and encourage you to work hard for the success you deserve. 
 
#BawseBook will not teach you how to survive life, because I don’t want you to simply survive. You are not in the middle of the ocean, floating on a door, holding on to Jack and waiting for someone to come and rescue you. You can do more than that. You have a toolbox filled with confidence, intelligence, power and resilience. You will not just survive, you will conquer… like a Bawse.
 
On March 28th, 2017, say goodbye to the version of yourself that is full of doubts and fears, and say hello to your inner Bawse.

ZQu3E0gU0ww.title: The #GirlLove Challenge
ZQu3E0gU0ww.description:
SHARE THIS ON FACEBOOK: http://on.fb.me/1JDocg6
TWEET THIS VIDEO: http://ctt.ec/aamUB
ABOUT MALALA FUND: https://www.malala.org/about

All original music belongs to One Direction. But these wonderful instrumentals were remade and mastered by:
Music by: Durrani Bros.
All Additional Instruments by: Paul Castro aka THE iDENTiTY CRiSiS (http://www.youtube.com/theidc)
And of course all the horrible singing was done by yours truly =) HEY! I DO COMEDY OKAY. 

Special thanks to Lindsey Stirling for the cameo, Humble the Poet for his amazing camera work and Symposium in Vaughan for letting us shoot in their awesome resto! 

--LYRICS--

-That's What Makes You Beautiful-
Your dress is short!
Don’t know what for!
Can see your knees when you walk through the door
Is that make up?
You wearing blush?
Go and change before I kick you in the butt!

Everyone kids dresses very proper
Everyone else but you….

Why don’t you wear all the clothes that I always get
like that nice scarf or the big pink turtleneck 
you wearing ten inch high heel and I bet
you don’t know
you look like a bloody mess

If only you saw what family sees
They don’t like big earrings, they like school degrees
only curve you should show is some round rotis
trust me I know….
that’s what makes you beautiful
ooo-ooo
that's what makes you beautiful!

-Story Of My Life-
Sitting in my backseat, are clothes that I have to change
I leave my house covered, put a dress on while I’m changing lanes
Mom told me when I left that I should be back home latest by nine
Seems to me that I’ll have to say my phone died and i lost track of time

And I’ll be gone, gone tonight
to meet my boyfriend, yeah I lied
Know I’m not supposed to talk to guys
But he’s just so damn fine…

The story of my life
i leave from home
In 10 minutes, I
hear my phone
It’s mom…I should have knownnnn…

The story of my life
I text my friend
I know my mom will call to just check in
Please lie. 
Say i’m in the washroom

-Steal My Girl-
She’s been my queen
since she was 16
she is my daughter
i am her papi ALRIGHT (ALRIGHT)

She is a doll
She do good in school
She never break rule
She always tell truth ALRIGHT (ALRIGHT)

I know, I know, I know for sure

Every boy want to steal my girl
Everybody want to call her late at night
But I am listening outside her door
and i know everything she does online

Everybody want to steal my girl
But she can’t lie to me you see
because i know her phone password
and always read her diary

Na na na na na na (oh, yeah)
Na na na na na na (alright)
Na na na na na na
Na na

She won’t lie to me! 

-Night Changes-
Going out tonight, changes into something else
My father doesn’t like that kind of dress
Everything you says to help, i’m blowing off

Calls from my mom, voice is screaming through the phone
She said just wait until I get home
Having no regrets it all I really want.

I’m only getting older damn it
it took 2 weeks for him to plan this
wanted one pic just to instagram it
I hate it when the night changes

Everything that I ever dreamed of
disappearing cause we break up
I’m not a kid dad, wont u wake up
how in hell did this night change up

Manjeet: you will never leave the house again.

i leave from home

wanted one pic just to instagram it

how in hell did this night change up

TFRwWpNFxWE.title: Terminator Genisys: The YouTube Chronicles in 360
TFRwWpNFxWE.description:
Watch me and other YouTubers save the world in a YouTube 360-degree video, from the perspective of the Terminator!

OrLXmxWvkj8.title: Forever in Our Hearts...
OrLXmxWvkj8.description:
RIP to one of the most amazing people I have ever had the honour of knowing. You were, are and always will be such a big part of me. Thank you for always smiling because it was infectious. Thank you for not only loving my silly ways but acting silly with me. I hope and pray that you are without pain and suffering now and that you will always look down on us. 

Thank you Nana Ji. If as a granddaughter I've ever made any mistakes, please forgive me. I love you always and you will never be forgotten.  

Bye for now. See you soon x
